# WHAT IT IS
#   MockRTC is the WebRTC-mocking sibling of mockttp (HTTP Toolkit's
#   HTTP mock peer + proxy).  It exposes a typed `MockRTC` peer API —
#   `.forPeer().onMessage(...).thenSend(...)`, `.thenEcho()`,
#   `.thenForwardTo(peer)`, `.thenWaitForOffer()`,
#   `.thenWaitForDuration(ms)`, `.thenClose()` — that lets you write
#   declarative WebRTC fixtures that intercept arbitrary
#   DataChannel and media traffic between real peers, modify it
#   in flight, drop it, fork it, replay it, or proxy it onward
#   to another peer.  Each rule is composed of a *matcher* and a
#   *handler*: matchers filter on `messageBetween(peerA, peerB)`,
#   `messageContains(...)`, `messageFrom(peer)`, etc., and handlers
#   transform, drop, delay, or echo.  Under the hood it speaks the
#   libdatachannel C++ WebRTC stack via `node-datachannel`, plus a
#   GraphQL admin server (port 45456 by default) that lets remote
#   clients in any language define rules over the wire — including
#   from the HTTP Toolkit GUI, which is the headline consumer.
#
#   The `mockrtc` CLI is a thin wrapper: it spawns the admin
#   server, sets environment variables that point client SDKs at
#   it, runs the configured test command, then tears the server
#   down when the test exits.  CI-friendly:  exit code mirrors
#   the inner command's exit code; SIGINT / SIGTERM are forwarded.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/admin-bin.ts argv
#                       parser; extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       httptoolkit/mockrtc/contents/src/
#                       admin-bin.ts`)
#
#   mockrtc -c <test command>
#
#   Options:
#     -c <CMD>                       Test command to run with the
#                                    MockRTC admin server up
#                                    (passed verbatim to a
#                                    `child_process.spawn(...,
#                                    {shell: true})` invocation;
#                                    quote multi-word commands)
#
#   Behavior:
#     • Starts a MockRTC admin server (GraphQL on default port).
#     • Spawns `<CMD>` with stdio inherited so test output is
#       visible.
#     • Forwards `<CMD>`'s exit code; if it died on a signal,
#       prints the signal name and exits 1.
#     • Cleanly stops the admin server on exit.
#
#   Standard auto-output:
#     Without `-c`, prints:
#       `Usage: mockrtc -c <test command>`
#     and exits 1.
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `node-datachannel ^0.12.0` declared in
#   package.json — `node-datachannel` is THE canonical Node
#   WebRTC binding maintained by Murat Doğan
#   (murat-dogan/node-datachannel, 600+ stars; native Node
#   bindings for paullouisageneau's libdatachannel C++ library,
#   the same WebRTC + DataChannel stack used by mediasoup, Jitsi,
#   Janus, BroadcastBox, and every production Node WebRTC SFU).
#   node-datachannel exposes the typed `PeerConnection`
#   constructor with `new PeerConnection(name, {iceServers,
#   iceTransportPolicy, certificateType, enableIceTcp,
#   enableIceUdpMux, maxMessageSize, mtu})`, every typed
#   `pc.setLocalDescription` / `pc.setRemoteDescription` /
#   `pc.addRemoteCandidate` / `pc.createDataChannel(label,
#   {protocol, reliable, ordered, negotiated, id, maxPacket
#   LifeTime, maxRetransmits})` / `pc.addTrack` / `pc.close`
#   request + response model, the typed `DataChannel` /
#   `Track` / `RtcpReceivingSession` primitives, callback
#   registration via
#   `pc.onLocalDescription` / `pc.onLocalCandidate` /
#   `pc.onStateChange` / `pc.onIceStateChange` /
#   `pc.onGatheringStateChange` / `pc.onDataChannel` /
#   `pc.onTrack`, the SDP munging helpers
#   (`pc.maxDataChannelId()`, `pc.maxMessageSize()`,
#   `pc.getRemoteFingerprint()`), the typed Media `Audio` /
#   `Video` description builders (`Audio(mid, direction)` with
#   `.addOpusCodec(...)` / `.addVP8Codec(...)` / `.addH264Codec(
#   ...)`), the WebSocket signaling helpers
#   (`WebSocket` / `WebSocketServer`), and the global
#   `setLocalCandidate` / `cleanup` / `preload` lifecycle hooks.
#   mockrtc's `src/webrtc/...` wraps `PeerConnection` per mock
#   peer, intercepts every offered DataChannel by attaching a
#   shadow `DataChannel` instance that the rule engine routes
#   through the matchers + handlers pipeline.  Verified via:
